SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 2146
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
5669S.03C KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal sections 96.192, 96.196, 195.417, 206.110, and 579.060, RSMo, and to enact in lieu
thereof seven new sections relating to health care providers, with penalty provisions.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Sections 96.192, 96.196, 195.417, 206.110, and
2 579.060, RSMo, are repealed and seven new sections enacted in
3 lieu thereof, to be known as sections 96.192, 96.196, 195.417,
4 206.110, 206.158, 376.417, and 579.060, to read as follows:
1 96.192. 1. The board of trustees of any hospital
2 authorized under subsection 2 of this section, and
3 established and organized under the provisions of sections
4 96.150 to 96.229, may invest up to [twenty-five] fifty
5 percent of [the hospital's] its funds not required for
6 immediate disbursement in obligations or for the operation
7 of the hospital [in any United States investment grade fixed
8 income funds or any diversified stock funds, or both] into:
